			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Perhaps I should be paying more attention to international law, since i believe that this falls under those stipulations.  The game is marketed worldwide, not California wide.<BR>
<BR>
Verant Cons:  The story in question was not distributed for the purpose of profit.  It was also not distributed to the general public, only to the select EQ community.  Therefore, in my opinion, Verant/Sony cannot invoke the law for the purpose of banning this person from the game; and on a more philosophical note, they are not qualified to judge this person's right to free speech.<BR>
<BR>
Verant Pros:  Verant is a Company which offers a service to the end of making a profit, this person is a customer of this company and Verant/Sony reserves the right to ban a person from play in this community for any reasons they see fit.<BR>
<BR>
Conclusion:  Verant/Sony is within their rights to ban this person, however i feel they are well outside of their rights by attempting to invoke the law.  Because they have made public their reason as such, they have violated this person's rights to free speech and are in danger of a lawsuit.  
				</font>
