				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Greetings, I reveiwed most of the messages posted here.I have also listened <BR>
to both sides of the issue and will comment in defence of both sides. Need I <BR>
remind Sony that property rights take a beating where fanfiction is concerned?<BR>
Final Fantasy, Zelda, Xmen, and Ranma 1/2 are examples of popular copy <BR>
writed material that has thousands of fanfictions written about them with no <BR>
legal actions taken. Many of them have NC-17 rateings and are as immoral as <BR>
possible. I also find it interesting that instead of takeing legal action against <BR>
someone whom they believed to be doing something illegal, they banned the <BR>
person instead. I am well aware of the fact that Sony acted within their legal <BR>
rights. Unfortunetly, to many people Sony did not let the matter be brought up <BR>
for debate. Instead letting a court of law rule on the matter they acted on their <BR>
own to punish the individual. One last comment on the subject of law. The law <BR>
is not made to keep people happy. The law is also not designed to decide what <BR>
is right and wrong or even to uphold what is right. The law is designed to keep <BR>
the peace. That is all it is made to do. Any arguements about morality are not <BR>
valid unless Sony decides they are. I'm sure many of you are not happy with <BR>
this as I am not but thats how it is. As far as fanfiction writers are concerned <BR>
none of them make any money of their stories. Many of them simply wish to <BR>
voice their opinions through stories and present the reader with their point of <BR>
view. Obviously some of their ideas can be offensive and hurtful, but we all <BR>
have the right to our own opinions. I also know that many players complain <BR>
that Sony doesn't listen to them and doesn't care about their opinions. I don't<BR>
believe that is how they feel. I think that many of them are just trying to <BR>
provide a quality game for us and for the most part I believe they have. I think<BR>
they have taken a fair and logical approach to the design of this game. <BR>
Unfortunetly, the fair approach is not always the easy or popular one. If <BR>
someone has a different opinion or a different point of view please prove me <BR>
wrong if they can. I try to see the matter from all sides but if I missed one I'd <BR>
like to know. Thank you for your time. <BR>
 <BR>
   
